article.headline: Lipscomb 77, Fisk 66
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Brian Fisk scored 19 points in leading Lipscomb to a 77-66 victory over Division III opponent Fisk on Saturday. Fisk (1-3) never led in the second half, but cut it to 51-46 on a three-point play by Jeff Anderson with 11:37 to go. Lipscomb (1-1) answered with an 8-2 spurt, capped by Brian Fisk's 3-pointer with 9:43 left to give the Bisons a 59-48 lead. The Bisons stretched the lead to 75-61 with 1:05 to play on a free throw by Jason Jackson, who finished with 12 points. Lipscomb also got 10 points each from Matt Jarboe and Chad Hartman. Marquis Patton scored 17 points for Fisk. Anderson finished with 14 points and Frank Dotson added 12 for the Bulldogs. The second half opened with a free throw by the Bulldogs after Lipscomb's Cameron Robinson received a technical foul for throwing the ball at a Fisk player after the first half buzzer.
